#13695
The war~
A small gust of wind consistantly drives into your body, sending chills
through even the hardest of hearts, as the sense of powerful evil still
lingers.  Weapons from long ago still lay on the ground here, but seem to
have faded away to nothing but a picture and a memory, allowing those who
have come to his hallowed ground to see the remnants of the war.  Signs of
fighting are everywhere, the ground stained a deep red with the blood of
mortal men and women who gave their life for this world.  A glow can be seen
from beyond the ridge to the north, filling the rim of the horizon with a
faint blue.  To the east and west are more signs of the battle, spreading it
wide over these fields of nothing.  
